            "answer_text": "Southern of Italy includes many provinces including Abruzzo, Apulia, Basilicata, Calabria, Campania, Molise, Corsica(Island) and Sicilia (island). There are old Albanian communities(orthodox) especially in Calabria and Sicilia who moved there since 14th and 15th century due to invasion of Ottomans. They still speak an older version of Albanian called \u2018arberesh\u2019 sane as the one spoken by Albanians(arvanitas) who moved same time (even earlier) to nowadays Greek areas. Most of them are blended in with Italians but still speak \u2018arberesh\u2019 which is one of the historical minorities languages spoken in southern Italy, along with Catalan, Calabrian Greek, Sardinian, Serbo-Croatian, etc. I would not say southern Italians have Albanian ancestral blood. ",
